##Grandma hard core, I'm sorry we didn't tell you

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Tang Qi, the paper

The 90-year-old "hard-core Grandma" , who moved the Internet, has now learned that her 60-year-old son, who took care of him for five days and five nights, has died of new coronary pneumonia.

The paper, which published a report on Feb. 8 titled "Oral Report on a 90-year-old man caring for his sick 60-year-old son, what supports her "hard core" , focused on a 90-year-old man from Wuhan. Her name is Xu Meiwu, her 64-year-old son was infected with new coronary pneumonia, in the hospital outpatient department after five days and five nights to wait for a bed, but because the condition aggravated into the ICU.

In fact, even before the report was published, the paper had learned from a doctor surnamed Wuhan Union Hospital at the Wuhan Union Hospital, xu Meiwu's son had died earlier.

On March 10, Dr. Lin posted a long essay on his microblog titled "I'm sorry I lied, " detailing his encounter with Xu Meiwu.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Screenshot

A letter that will never arrive

According to Lin, he met Xu Meiwu at 2 a.m. on Feb. 3. The old man took the responsibility of caring for his 64-year-old son, who was diagnosed with new crown pneumonia at the time, so as not to infect other family members, it wasn't until her son was admitted that she was able to come to the clinic alone for a CT scan.

Dr. Lin wrote in the above-mentioned article that while waiting for the results, Xu Meiwu borrowed paper and a pen from a nurse, he wrote a message that touched the hearts of countless netizens: "My son, we must hold on, be strong and conquer the disease. ". Cooperate with the doctor to treat, respiratory discomfort, to endure a, in order to recover. If your blood pressure is normal and you have oxygen in your nostrils, call your doctor. I forgot to give cash. I asked the doctor to bring five hundred dollars. I asked someone to buy daily necessities."

Xu Meiwu once told The Paper news that after her son was sent to the emergency room on Feb. 3, his family couldn't stay with him all the time. In a hurry, she borrowed a pen from the nurse and thought of writing a letter to her son so that he could be treated with ease. She desperately wanted to tell her son that his mother didn't want him to care as long as he lived.

Xu Meiwu said, "because I live with my son and have been in close contact with him for five days and nights in the hospital, the whole family is now worried about whether I have an infection. If I get a negative nucleic acid test and live, it doesn't matter to me if I get a positive result. I just hope that my son, who is still in critical condition, can be saved so that I have more hope to live a few more years. Even if it means selling the house, I want his life back."

Later, Xu Meiwu wrote the letter did not pass to his son. In an interview with thepaper.cn on Feb. 7, she did not know that her son had died at 5:40 p.m. the day after she wrote the letter.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Grandma Xu borrowed a pen and paper from a nurse and left a message for her son. @ Dr. Lin of pediatric endocrinology

The doctor who "lied" for her

On Feb. 12, thepaper.cn learned from Xu's family that Xu's nucleic acid test had yielded negative results, and that he had been ruled out of infection with new crown pneumonia, but that he had been hospitalized for advanced age and low fever.

Lin also said on Weibo that at the time he told his colleagues, including Xu's son's bed doctor, not to tell her the cruel truth. The old man could not bear it.

On March 9, when Dr. Lin asked Xu Meiwu's family about the old man's condition, he learned that his family had already told her the painful news. The old man was devastated.

"The reason why I chose today (March 10) to tell you this news is mainly because it has been two consecutive days and the number of newly confirmed cases is less than 100. People can breathe a little easier and perhaps accept the cruel truth. Then the old people also learned the news, and despite the sadness, life goes on, " Dr. Lin wrote on his Weibo Account.

At noon on March 9, The Paper news also learned from Xu Meiwu's family that the old man had learned of his son's death. According to the family, doctors and nurses treated the old man very well. Her condition was stable, and her mood was well adjusted.

Xu will officially celebrate her 90th birthday on March 26, but her family told The Paper it was unclear whether she would be able to leave the hospital before her birthday.

The new crown pneumonia outbreak changed the fate of many ordinary families, in the early stages of the epidemic, for patients, a disease like a mountain, a bed is a ray of light.

On March 10, the number of newly confirmed cases of pneumonia in Wuhan dropped sharply to 17. On the same day, Wuhan actually put into use 15 shelter hospital all the rest cabin.

Also on March 10, the sunshine in Wuhan was really good. "We have lost so much in this epidemic, but the dead are gone. We have to wipe away our tears and walk hand in hand, " Lin said.
